            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <h3>Is raw meat safe for my pet? What about bacteria like Salmonella?</h3>
                    <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>Yes, raw meat is safe when sourced from reputable suppliers and handled properly. Dogs and cats have evolved to handle bacteria in raw meat through:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Highly acidic stomach environment (pH 1-2)</li>
                        <li>Short digestive transit time (4-6 hours)</li>
                        <li>Strong immune systems adapted for raw consumption</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Proper handling includes: keeping meat frozen until use, thawing in refrigerator, using within 24-48 hours of thawing, and maintaining clean feeding areas.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <h3>Will raw bones break my dog's teeth or cause choking?</h3>
                    <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p><strong>RAW bones are safe and beneficial</strong> - they're soft, pliable, and provide essential nutrients. It's COOKED bones that become brittle and dangerous.</p>
                    <p>Safe raw bones include:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Chicken necks and wings (for smaller dogs)</li>
                        <li>Duck necks and frames</li>
                        <li>Lamb ribs and necks</li>
                        <li>Beef ribs (for larger dogs)</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Always supervise bone consumption and choose appropriate sizes for your pet.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <h3>Can puppies and kittens eat raw food?</h3>
                    <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>Yes! Raw feeding is excellent for growing puppies and kittens. Young animals actually handle raw food better than adults due to stronger stomach acid.</p>
                    <p>Special considerations for young pets:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Feed smaller, more frequent meals (3-4 times daily)</li>
                        <li>Start with softer proteins like chicken or turkey</li>
                        <li>Increase calcium content for proper bone development</li>
                        <li>Monitor weight gain and adjust portions accordingly</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
