                    <h3>How much raw food should I feed my pet?</h3>
                    <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>General guidelines per day based on ideal body weight:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Adult dogs:</strong> 2-3% of body weight</li>
                        <li><strong>Active/working dogs:</strong> 3-4% of body weight</li>
                        <li><strong>Puppies:</strong> 5-10% of body weight (varies by age)</li>
                        <li><strong>Adult cats:</strong> 3-5% of body weight</li>
                        <li><strong>Kittens:</strong> 5-10% of body weight</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Monitor your pet's body condition and adjust portions accordingly. You should be able to feel ribs easily but not see them prominently.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <h3>What's the 80/10/10 rule?</h3>
                    <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>The 80/10/10 rule is the foundation of balanced raw feeding:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>80% Muscle Meat:</strong> Chicken, beef, lamb, fish, etc.</li>
                        <li><strong>10% Organ Meat:</strong> Half should be liver, half other organs (kidney, heart, lung)</li>
                        <li><strong>10% Edible Bones:</strong> Chicken necks, wings, lamb ribs, etc.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>This ratio mimics the nutritional profile of whole prey and ensures complete nutrition over time.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <h3>How often should I feed my pet and should I fast them?</h3>
                    <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p><strong>Feeding frequency:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Puppies under 6 months: 3-4 meals daily</li>
                        <li>Dogs 6-12 months: 2-3 meals daily</li>
                        <li>Adult dogs: 1-2 meals daily</li>
                        <li>Cats: 2-3 smaller meals daily</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Fasting:</strong> Optional weekly 24-hour fasts can benefit adult dogs by improving digestion and mimicking natural feeding patterns. Never fast puppies, kittens, pregnant/nursing mothers, or pets with health conditions.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

