                    <h3>How do I transition my pet from kibble to raw food?</h3>
                    <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>Two main approaches:</p>
                    <p><strong>Gradual transition (7-14 days):</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Days 1-3: 75% old food, 25% raw</li>
                        <li>Days 4-6: 50% old food, 50% raw</li>
                        <li>Days 7-9: 25% old food, 75% raw</li>
                        <li>Days 10+: 100% raw</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Cold turkey (recommended for healthy adult pets):</strong> Switch immediately to raw, often causing fewer digestive issues as different foods require different digestive processes.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <h3>What should I expect during the transition period?</h3>
                    <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>Normal transition effects (usually resolve within 1-2 weeks):</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Loose stools initially, then firmer, smaller stools</li>
                        <li>Temporary decrease in appetite</li>
                        <li>Increased water consumption</li>
                        <li>Different stool odor and frequency</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Contact a vet if you notice: persistent vomiting, bloody stools, severe lethargy, or refusal to eat for more than 24 hours.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
